Does ```desc``` also represent the number of descendant nodes for a node? Then it is unnecessary to take it into account when you want to count the sum of value of nodes greater than n. You should sum their keys. Besides, since your function doesn&#39;t modify the tree, there is no need to consider rotation.

Here is my advice code in recursion.
```
    int SumGreater(Node root, int x) {
        int res = 0;
     
        while (root != null) {
            if (root.key &gt; x) {
                res += root.key;
                res += SumGreater(root.right, x);
                root = root.left;
            } else {
                root = root.right;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
```

